<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="470" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1335,1613]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1372,1397]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Haacke" box="[323,489,1372,1397]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Haacke, W. D. (1965) Additional notes on the Herpetology of South West Africa with descriptions of two new subspecies of geckos. Cimbebasia, 11, 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="1965">
Haacke (
<number box="[423,481,1372,1397]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1965.0">1965</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
originally described this form as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[1052,1179,1372,1396]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis box="[1052,1179,1372,1396]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">A. africana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and it has maintained this rank since (
<bibRefCitation author="Mertens" box="[339,503,1408,1432]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Mertens, R. (1971) Die Herpetofauna Sudwest - Afrikas. Abhandlungen der Senckenbergischen naturforschenden Gesellschaft, 529, 1 - 110." type="journal article" year="1971">
Mertens 
<number box="[444,503,1408,1432]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1971.0">1971</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Branch" box="[519,669,1407,1432]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Branch, W. R. (1981) An annotated checklist of the lizards of the Cape Province, South Africa. Annals of the Cape Provincial Museums (Natural History), 13, 141 - 167." type="journal article" year="1981">Branch 1981</bibRefCitation>
, 1988, 
<number box="[759,818,1408,1432]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1998.0">1998</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Onderstall" box="[834,1022,1407,1432]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Onderstall, D. (1984) Descriptions of two new subspecies of Afroedura pondolia (Hewitt) and a discussion of species groups within the genus (Reptilia: Gekkonidae). Annals of the Transvaal Museum, 33, 497 - 509." type="journal article" year="1984">
Onderstall 
<number box="[962,1022,1408,1432]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Branch 
<emphasis box="[1129,1182,1407,1432]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[1200,1259,1408,1432]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1988.0">1988</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Griffin" box="[1275,1424,1407,1432]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Griffin, M. (2003) Annotated Checklist and Provisional National Conservation Status of Namibian Reptiles. Namibia Scientific Society, Windhoek, [ii] + 169 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Griffin 
<number box="[1364,1424,1408,1432]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), although chiefly because this poorly known taxon has not been reviewed subsequently. Under modern species concepts, the differences between the supposed subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Haacke 1965" authorityName="Haacke" authorityYear="1965" box="[891,1206,1479,1504]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis box="[891,1022,1480,1504]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">A. africana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Haacke" box="[1042,1198,1479,1504]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Haacke, W. D. (1965) Additional notes on the Herpetology of South West Africa with descriptions of two new subspecies of geckos. Cimbebasia, 11, 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="1965">
Haacke 
<number box="[1141,1198,1479,1504]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1965.0">1965</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(see above) would generally be accepted as evidence of specific distinctness, especially in light of the large disjunctions between the forms and their likely low vagility (
<bibRefCitation author="Mouton" box="[551,831,1551,1576]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Mouton, P. le F. N. &amp; Mostert, D. P. (1985) Description of a new species of Afroedura (Loveridge) (Reptilia: Gekkonidae) from the south - western Cape. South African Journal of Zoology, 20, 246 - 249." type="journal article" year="1985">
Mouton &amp; Mostert 
<number box="[772,831,1551,1576]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Jacobsen" box="[843,1011,1551,1576]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Jacobsen, N. H. G. (1997) Family Gekkonidae, Genus Afroedura. In: Van Wyk, J. H. (Ed.), Proceedings of the FitzSimons Commemorative Symposium, South African Lizards: 50 years of Progress and Third H. A. A. Symposium on African Herpetology, Transvaal Museum, Pretoria, South Africa, 11 - 15 October 1993. Herpetological Association of Africa, Stellenbosch, pp. 34 - 39." type="journal article" year="1997">
Jacobsen 
<number box="[951,1011,1552,1576]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). On this basis we here recognize this taxon at the rank of full species.
</paragraph>
